The paper deals with the problem of compressing and storing information about minimum cuts in a network, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves graph theory and algorithms for finding minimum cuts, which are topics in network analysis (cs.NE) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of mimicking networks and the bounds on their size involve combinatorial and probabilistic arguments, which are techniques used in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT).
